{"id":503821,"global_id":"Z2lkOi8vaGFja2Vyb25lL1JlcG9ydC81MDM4MjE=","url":"https://hackerone.com/reports/503821","title":"Assertion `col \u003e= 0 \u0026\u0026 col \u003c line-\u003ecols' failed, process aborted while streaming ouput from remote server","state":"Closed","substate":"resolved","severity_rating":"low","readable_substate":"Resolved","created_at":"2019-03-01T15:32:17.595Z","submitted_at":"2019-03-01T15:32:17.595Z","is_member_of_team?":false,"is_organization_group_member?":false,"is_triager?":false,"reporter":{"disabled":false,"username":"geeknik","url":"/geeknik","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/jgjvp6dlesp661w5ashvoami0j3c/c8a1698ff707a5e3e8a91a3484838363845daac68cb82c86d55c9e2d44d67b67"},"is_me?":false,"cleared":false,"verified":true,"hackerone_triager":false,"hacker_mediation":false},"team":{"id":36864,"url":"https://hackerone.com/putty_h1c","handle":"putty_h1c","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/036/864/2391b6ba38d30ce95133befbf8f31851c7874a32_original.png/235acf2ba808c3a51a94888fb977392c26f8fb0ccf77a81a4546c5e4065c06f1","medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/036/864/2391b6ba38d30ce95133befbf8f31851c7874a32_original.png/3f1ab5c6a9b6dadada1e6c8121700b884388bd0a43471fee1897a38ce57d0b2c"},"permissions":[],"submission_state":"paused","default_currency":"usd","awards_miles":false,"offers_bounties":true,"state":"public_mode","only_cleared_hackers":false,"pentest_feature_enabled?":false,"pentest_retesting_ends_at":null,"profile":{"name":"PuTTY (European Commission - DIGIT)","twitter_handle":"","website":"http://ec.europa.eu","about":""}},"has_bounty?":true,"can_view_team":true,"can_view_report":true,"is_external_bug":false,"is_published":false,"is_participant":false,"has_collaborators":false,"submitted_by_team_member":false,"submitted_with_assistant":false,"stage":4,"public":true,"visibility":"full","cve_ids":[],"singular_disclosure_disabled":false,"disclosed_at":"2019-11-03T16:39:02.863Z","bug_reporter_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2019-10-04T16:38:54.445Z","team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":null,"comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"**Summary:**\nDuring the course of testing putty-0.70-2019-03-01.e0a7697 on Fedora 29 compiled with clang version 7.0.1 (Fedora 7.0.1-4.fc29), we discovered it was possible to abort a remote client by streaming data at it in such a way as to trigger an assertion failure in terminal.c.\n\n```\nputty: terminal.c:259: void clear_cc(termline *, int): Assertion `col \u003e= 0 \u0026\u0026 col \u003c line-\u003ecols' failed.\nAborted (core dumped)\n```\n\n**Description:** \nAn assertion is a statement that a predicate (Boolean-valued function, i.e. a true–false expression) is always true at that point in code execution. It can help a programmer read the code, help a compiler compile it, or help the program detect its own defects. \n\nIn this case, we can trigger the PuTTY client, using escape codes streamed from a remote connection, to resize itself in such a way as to trigger this Assertion Failure which aborts the client. \n\n## Steps To Reproduce:\n1. Download https://tartarus.org/~simon/putty-snapshots/putty.tar.gz\n2. Extract putty.tar.gz\n3. change to the putty directory created in step 2.\n3. `CC=clang CXX=clang++ ./configure \u0026\u0026 make -j5`\n4. Launch PuTTY with your favorite debugger.\n5. Connect to a remote host of your choice\n6. On remote host: mkdir corpus \u0026\u0026 git clone https://gitlab.com/akihe/radamsa.git \u0026\u0026 cd radamsa \u0026\u0026 make \u0026\u0026 sudo make install \u0026\u0026 cd ~\n7. On remote host, upload the attached JPG file to the corpus directory we created in step 4. \n8. On remote host type while true; radamsa -s 911 -o - -n inf corpus/*; done and let run until crashes.\n\n## Supporting Material/References:\nI've uploaded the core dump that happened at the time of the crash.\n\n## Impact\n\nDenial of service, crash, loss of data contained in scroll back","weakness":{"id":2,"name":"Memory Corruption - Generic"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[{"id":433620,"file_name":"not_kitty.jpg","expiring_url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/000/433/620/b8ffd93524a5e49f5894e839a218679fd97d9ca4/not_kitty.jpg?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%22not_kitty.jpg%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%27not_kitty.jpg\u0026response-content-type=image%2Fjpeg\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQGK6FURQQGZ6LTSB%2F20260429%2Fus-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20260429T091908Z\u0026X-Amz-Expires=3600\u0026X-Amz-Security-Token=IQoJb3JpZ2luX2VjECgaCXVzLXdlc3QtMiJHMEUCIQC7mqe46kPhJeVkT%2BfOYRKXUga5A2lKJha3jedcj2dbrAIgZYk%2BllrT%2FPgvgfWFGwYZfTQUiZvbn1zWZRAPbx5dFQgquwUI8f%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2FARADGgwwMTM2MTkyNzQ4NDkiDIxgP0T6EsSYlHCEAiqPBWnwK3BpWWlBO5SUOYmGLWgtu5CiVqHv04NUQStRYf9idDNWhyUG%2Br1B%2BXVsgn1%2B8meqMDKS0i86vF3ZvHhx8KEghsYuiuTmF2JZQCdzbiaevkFLTyyBT0LlTa2u%2BDzTOoOAIcQ4IO1XRf37kKvkDeZXTp0%2B999jyfZJ38pjnbr4pYpErtV2mBpGeH4plXxxXT2EyIsZjeGYwQXBt5WBgBmJxzDMqWMayu4EUbV75x3b0Jr7f1EyBZgz%2FgFz%2B1C8F7RFxjIhYiIQEe6bDKEz6GzIJNvyhX4jMF9ntXu09d9RVyoMezSLolZ5MpFpHs0OeokGjXaWd18iiXmz4jzLtj0Dt9Vu0T5sC20m1AAWZiGo1DOdjFIdspXBwFk4p6N%2FVuaDgMue7n9GW17x20RebR5UeOEN3fSH%2FnIaHiZ9GHyU32Ric8J79A9FVu7p8ohVWZRzV7RyNjcsL%2BbsNEWBVDBriyX1Jgsiq4Lx81C8DOK8HLhpIPXPFNyR7ASG2u0E9giMg7HuEUPXckCxpWbExJNxg6g90Lj5vsafBnlJjySktOO8jYaCo3R2PvNTeubfofmi8b9WBHiwMu%2Bt6h78yqkw%2BFNtq8FiUwHmGszvZpG3NOmlQ38vaIGGYWIntZC1Bt%2BmZEsJUTJl1YUakqErR%2BIgOjqhA9UxEMYyeUXYm2eRoHjP9zG%2BjYQR04QhIOFzewy0nFFwwr4ta17sL7nb4uIcq5RqlMKpdO8bLlJ%2FVSnAi%2BVs%2BTo4tA7ShiIltdxTEhiW3Bn29nKZZMmHU6h3mydwqkjzjBp0P3MqK0L9xo%2Fftlyl7YrU482eMC2txqAqc35EWmvRMjrWKZsFLck8fAToRTO9tZRABK%2BOlSCd%2F9kw%2FfTGzwY6sQGstRwnhWyPWAiic9ajSWnMnxjKBEs